Global Automotive Plastic Extruded Parts Market Insights
Automotive Plastic Extruded Parts Market size was valued at USD 30.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 48.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Automotive Plastic Extruded Parts Market Overview
The global automotive plastic extruded parts market is projected to reach a market value of USD 18.5 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The increasing demand for lightweight, durable, and cost-effective materials in the automotive sector is a key factor driving this market. Additionally, the shift towards electric vehicles (EVs) and the growing trend of vehicle customization are influencing the market's expansion. The automotive plastic extruded parts are widely used in exterior and interior parts, including trims, bumpers, and dashboards, contributing to the market growth. Increasing regulatory pressure for fuel-efficient and environmentally friendly vehicles is also a driving factor for the adoption of plastic materials in automotive manufacturing.

